SIMPLE: electrician
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: electrician
<hw>e`lec*tri"cian</hw> <pr>(⟦emac⟧`l⟦ecr⟧k*tr⟦icr⟧sh"⟦ait⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An investigator of electricity; one
versed in the science of electricity.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a technician who installs, repairs, or maintains
electrical wiring or electrical devices, especially in
buildings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def> a person who is licensed by a governmental board to
install electrical wiring and devices in structures; called also a
<altname>licensed electrician</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electricity</ent>⟦br⟧
